</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amanojyaku>Amano Jyaku</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Stylin' Hentai Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 1157<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/17/02 2:20:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10762.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/xhead.gif height=83 width=103></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior damage question</span><hr size=1> I dual wield almost 100% of the time. Seems to do more damage overall plus helps keep the agro on you..<br>
<br>
 -Amano <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amanojyaku>Amano Jyaku</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/17/02 2:22:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminutemanaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minute Manaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ASSIST DAMMIT!!!</span><br>  Posts: 1572<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/17/02 2:54:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10762.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior damage question</span><hr size=1> Whatever creates the most aggro.  Warriors primary job, imo, is to keep the mob on him.  Offense is the rogue or monks job in my groups.  Yes, often the more damage you do will generate more aggro but not in all cases.  For instance I may take a weapon that has a bit lower DPS because it proc's something that generates an extreme amount of aggro (i.e. stun or snare.)<br>
<br>
However, to answer your question directly.  Even after the recent table changes for 2 handed weapons I still have found that my 1 handers do better as well.  Don't discount a good 1 hander though.  A lot of people discount them because of how slow they are, but if you put them to a log parser many of them can easily dish more overall damage, especially when you start tackin on Crits &amp; Doubles (Or triples at 60). <p><br>
