<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42859">My Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uveranonwindseeker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veranon Windseeker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hem.passagen.se/trench/sr/icon1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Administrator</font></span><br>  Posts: 1595<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/17/02 2:57:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10762.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior damage question</span><hr size=1> most warriors go for dual wield for a few reasons.<br>
<br>
1. Higher damage<br>
2. More proc's to keep mobs aggro on you cause of the shorter delay and the fact that there's two weapons that can proc<br>
3. More hp/ac on most 1h than the 2h when pairing up two 1h. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21834 target=_document >
Veranon Windseeker &lt;Silent Redemption&gt;</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urheims.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rheims</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 393<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/17/02 5:25:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10762.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior damage question</span><hr size=1> I agree with all of the above but would add this:<br>
<br>
Sometimes you are not supposed to be taunting. Such as on a raid where there is a designated main tank and you are merely there to do damage and be a backup replacement main tank if he should die. This is a very common situation for a warrior to find himself in, especially in the high 40s through mid 50s period. In that situation 2h slash is useful and fun, it can keep agro down while you still dish out some damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uloyalhulk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LoyalHulk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/18/02 9:39:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10762.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=HTTP://games.sphynx.com/gokou.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior damage question</span><hr size=1> Two handed weapons taunt VERY well.   It is easier for me to steal aggro from the MA with a two handed weapon than when I duel wield.  <br>
<br>
It's all up to you how you want to dish out your damage.  Two handers + is the increased damage, the negatives are if you miss you do ALOT less damage.  Duel wielding is nice because even if you miss a lot you still do a lot of damage.<br>
<br>
Certain things to keep in mind.  Certain 1handers are king for drawing aggro (ie Willsapper, etc etc).  Also, I would wait on using a weapon like Tantors Tusk till your higher level.  The damage bonus ratio plus higher level group hastes make this a more effective high level weapon than if a lower level would try to use it.<br>
<br>
Also, keep a fast good damaging weapon in your main hand.  (Defiant, Lammy, etc etc)  and then put a slighty slower more damaging weapon in your off hand.<br>
Good combo's pre-epic are    <br>
Main Hand: Defiance, Lammy, Captain's Gaurd Mallet, Jade Mace, etc etc.<br>
Off Hand:  Blade of the Green Dragon/Black Dragon, Frostbringer, etc etc.<br>
<br>
Two handers to look for are ones that have a close damage/delay ratio.  Also, keep in mind the delay bonus is directly related to the amount of delay the weapon has.  Even though a Weighted Axe is a almost worthless weapon in normal combat it is King using the /disc furious.<br>
<br>
Hope that answer's some of you warrior questions. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Loyal Hulk<br>
